              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                Yongle Emperor gained the upper hand in his campaigns against Oirat and Eastern Mongols but failed to destroy them due to their mobility in the steppe. Han Chinese couldn't stand the tough environment and the erratic cavalry warfare. It's inevitable that the rivalry between Mongols and Ming China lasted until Manchu came in to tip the balance.
